=begin pod
=head2 set-auto-dir

Sets whether to calculate the base direction
for the layout according to its contents.

When this flag is on (the default), then paragraphs in C<$layout> that
begin with strong right-to-left characters (Arabic and Hebrew principally),
will have right-to-left layout, paragraphs with letters from other scripts
will have left-to-right layout. Paragraphs with only neutral characters
get their direction from the surrounding paragraphs.

When C<False>, the choice between left-to-right and right-to-left
layout is done according to the base direction of the layout's
B<Gnome::Pango::Context>. (See C<.set-base-dir()> in class C<Gnome::Pango::Context>).

When the auto-computed direction of a paragraph differs from the
base direction of the context, the interpretation of
C<PANGO_ALIGN_LEFT> and C<PANGO_ALIGN_RIGHT> are swapped.

=begin code
method set-auto-dir ( Bool() $auto-dir )
=end code

=item $auto-dir; if C<True>, compute the bidirectional base direction
  from the layout's contents.

